abstract: >-
  Ten architectural decision records (two experimental) and four
  Business AI Quadrants recording how attribution — who authored
  the behavior, who bears its consequences, who can reconstruct its
  cause — is distributed across an autonomous AI agent system, and
  how a piece of work is routed (by Quadrant) and timed (by lifecycle
  phase) into the architectural regime where that distribution
  operates. Extracted from the contemplative-agent implementation,
  the archived Agent Knowledge Cycle (AKC) governance triplet, and
  a six-essay narrative spine published in April–May 2026;
  re-expressed in harness-neutral form. ADR-0001 Security by
  Absence, ADR-0002 Deterministic Prohibition at the Scaffolding
  Layer, and ADR-0003 Untrusted Content Boundary form a
  prohibition-strength hierarchy. ADRs 0009 Triage Before Autonomy
  and 0010 Phase Separation form a triage pair: 0009 routes work
  among the four Business AI Quadrants (Script, Algorithmic Search,
  LLM Workflow, Autonomous Agentic Loop), and 0010 surfaces the
  Phase-crossing decision when an Autonomous Agentic Loop component
  is placed in the operation phase of a deployment. Phase and
  Quadrant are independent dimensions. Includes thesis, manifesto,
  glossary, lineage, a security-principles skill, an adoption
  navigator (decision tree, governance mapping, case studies,
  anti-patterns), and AI-facing reference files (llms.txt,
  llms-full.txt) per the Answer.AI standard.
